The pseudolamellate operculum seen in this species is unexpected. This is a feature associated with the Barahona-Tiburon annulariid taxa, which are believed to be only distantly related to the group covered here (
Skomrock, 2014
). This appears to be a case of convergent evolution in the operculum of this family. In this complex it has only been found in this species.
